  <h3 class="c-left c-font-lowercase c-font-sbold">International</h3>

  <p>According to Fed’s semiannual monetary policy report to the Congress, the US economy grew at a strong pace
    in 2018, slightly below 3.0%, noting that they do not expect to perform upward adjustments to their interest
    rate in the short term. On the other hand, inflation  remained close to the Fed’s longer-run goal of 2.0% for
    2018.</p>
  <p>After several meetings between US and China negotiators, the trade war between both countries seems to be
    breaking down with the greater potential for agreement, which could benefit market stability, as well as
    enhance world economic growth through a more liberalized trade relationship.</p>
  <p>After the signing of the trade agreement between the United States, Mexico and Canada at the end of the
    previous federal administration, private foreign direct investment in the region seems to pick up its
    momentum, making the USMCA an important catalyst for economic growth in the region.</p>

  <h3 class="c-left c-font-lowercase c-font-sbold">National</h3>

  <p>During 2018, national GDP grew below 2.3% according to the Mexican National Institute of Statistics and
    Geography (Instituto Nacional de Estadística y Geografía – INEGI). Meanwhile, private sector specialists
    surveyed by Banxico, in January, maintained their GDP growth forecast of 1.8% YoY for 2019. On the other
    hand, the Consumer Confidence Index reached all-time high levels, fueling the expectation of a greater
    economic dynamism during the first months of the year.</p>

  <p>Banxico’s monetary policy decision at the end of the previous year to increase the reference rate to 8.25%,
    following the Fed’s upward adjustment and current balance of risks for inflation at that moment. However,
    during the last meeting held in February this year, Banxico’s Board was more dovish in essence, leaving
    the reference rate unchanged, recognizing the inflation improvement in January 2019 (4.37%).</p>

  <h3 class="c-left c-font-lowercase c-font-sbold">Industry</h3>

